<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Remarks.</emphasis>
Male specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[574,645,188,213]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[656,709,188,212]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Pará</collectingRegion>
, Caxiuanã have a much reduced male dorsal forewing iridescent band. This band is absent in two specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[742,795,224,248]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Pará</collectingRegion>
, Carajás and 
<collectingRegion box="[957,1074,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, Imperatriz. Inasmuch as these specimens markedly differ from those of other localities, we tentatively assign them to 
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1388,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="actorion" subSpecies="occulta">
<emphasis box="[1198,1388,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">actorion occulta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but recognize that this should be re-visited when additional specimens become available. It would be of interest to confirm the existence of a north-south cline within 
<taxonomicName box="[746,932,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="actorion" subSpecies="occulta">
<emphasis box="[746,932,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">actorion occulta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with regard to the size and presence of the male dorsal forewing iridescent band.
</paragraph>
